I'm surprised that we don't see more of these issues being reported to
the public since they are relatively common.

There are MANY mailing scripts out there that allow malicious users to
abuse - otherwise not vulnerable to relay - mail servers for
spamming/phishing purposes.

For those interested in this topic I hope you find the following paper
and advisory educational:

http://www.procheckup.com/PDFs/auditing_mailing_scripts.pdf
http://www.procheckup.com/Vulnerability_PR07-21.php

